This paper is about a methodology for summarization from multiple documents, which involves the identification of cross-document relations among textual elements. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on textual analysis and natural language processing, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.IR and cs.AI.
